services — service unit files

LOCATION
  /etc/services/<id>.cfg

FORMAT
  return {
    id          = "<short id>",
    description = "<one-line description>",
    exec        = "/sys/svc/<id>.lua",
    args        = { ... },
    after       = { "dep1", "dep2" },
    conflicts   = { "peer1", ... },
    caps        = { "*" },
    restart     = "on_failure" | "always" | "one_shot",
    autostart   = true | false,
    env         = { K = "V" },
  }

DESCRIPTION
  Read at boot by /sys/svc/init.lua and after that by /bin/svc on
  demand. The supervisor topo-sorts by `after`, spawns each unit in
  its own process, and restarts according to `restart`.

  conflicts is the optional cooperative-stop list: starting this
  service stops any peer in this list first.

EXAMPLES
  See /etc/services/{logd,sessiond,uid}.cfg in the source tree.

SEE ALSO
  svc(1)
